WEBVTT

00:07.928 --> 00:11.892
April: THERE'S A THING WE SAY
WHEN SOMEONE DIES.

00:15.346 --> 00:18.849
WE SAY IT
TO THE PATIENT'S FAMILY.

00:22.693 --> 00:26.197
Amelia: THERE ARE
ON-CALL ROOMS FOR THAT.

00:31.452 --> 00:34.495
WE SAY,
"I'M SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS."

00:34.495 --> 00:37.618
WITH TYPE II, WE'RE DEALING
WITH LOW BIRTH WEIGHT,

00:37.618 --> 00:40.211
UNDERDEVELOPED LUNGS,
SWALLOWING PROBLEMS,

00:40.211 --> 00:41.872
RESPIRATORY PROBLEMS.

00:41.872 --> 00:44.965
IF CARRIED TO TERM,
TYPE II INFANTS TYPICALLY DIE

00:44.965 --> 00:47.508
WITHIN A FEW HOURS OF DELIVERY,
SOMETIMES DAYS.

00:47.508 --> 00:51.432
YOUR BABY'S ALSO AT HIGH RISK
FOR INTRAUTERINE FRACTURING.

00:51.432 --> 00:53.224
I'M SORRY.
I'M SORRY.

00:53.224 --> 00:55.596
UM, DID YOU SAY
INTRAUTERINE?

00:55.596 --> 00:57.017
YES.
MY B--

00:57.017 --> 01:01.522
MY BABY'S BONES
ARE BREAKING INSIDE OF MY BELLY?

01:01.522 --> 01:03.604
THE PLACE
HE'S SUPPOSED TO BE SAFE,

01:03.604 --> 01:05.186
HIS -- HIS BONES ARE BREAKING.

01:05.186 --> 01:09.450
[ Voice breaking ] NO, I JUST --
UM, C-CAN HE FEEL IT?

01:09.450 --> 01:10.741
HIS BONES BREAKING?

01:10.741 --> 01:12.863
I MEAN,
HE CAN FEEL IT, RIGHT?

01:15.075 --> 01:17.408
SO, HE'S IN --
HE'S IN PAIN.

01:17.408 --> 01:20.201
AGAIN, I AM SO SORRY.

01:20.201 --> 01:26.207
IT'S A PAT LITTLE PHRASE,
AND AN EMPTY ONE.

01:26.207 --> 01:28.669
[ INDISTINCT TALKING,
MONITOR BEEPING ]

01:28.669 --> 01:30.671
Man: CLEAR!

01:30.671 --> 01:32.012
IT DOESN'T BEGIN TO COVER

01:32.012 --> 01:34.175
WHAT'S ACTUALLY HAPPENING
TO THEM.

01:34.175 --> 01:36.387
Man: CLEAR.

01:36.387 --> 01:40.100
IT LETS US EMPATHIZE
WITHOUT FORCING US

01:40.100 --> 01:42.893
TO FEEL
THEIR DEVASTATION OURSELVES.

01:45.686 --> 01:46.857
IT PROTECTS US...

01:46.857 --> 01:48.068
Man:
TIME OF DEATH...

01:48.068 --> 01:50.151
[ WOMAN WAILS ]

01:50.151 --> 01:52.733
...FROM FEELING THAT PAIN.

01:52.733 --> 01:56.737
THAT DARK, SINKING,
RELENTLESS PAIN --

01:56.737 --> 01:59.830
THE KIND
THAT CAN EAT YOU ALIVE.

01:59.830 --> 02:02.833
AND EVERY DAY,
I THANK GOD FOR THAT.

02:16.177 --> 02:18.179
[ DOOR OPENS ]

02:20.181 --> 02:21.812
I THOUGHT
THEY WENT HOME.

02:21.812 --> 02:23.764
THEY WANTED
TO TALK SOME MORE.

02:23.764 --> 02:26.026
I'M NOT SURE IT HELPED.
WHY DIDN'T YOU CALL ME?

02:26.026 --> 02:27.027
I MEAN, I CAN HELP THEM.

02:27.027 --> 02:28.068
THEY NEED SOMEONE
WHO KNOWS THEM

02:28.068 --> 02:30.070
AND WHO CARES ABOUT THEM
AND WHO CAN MAKE IT --

02:30.070 --> 02:31.232
WHO CAN MAKE IT WHAT?

02:31.232 --> 02:33.194
NICE.

02:33.194 --> 02:35.696
I WANT TO MAKE IT
AS NICE FOR THEM AS IT CAN BE.

02:35.696 --> 02:36.737
AND YOU'RE NOT NICE.

02:36.737 --> 02:38.489
YOU REALLY CARE ABOUT THEM,
DON'T YOU?

02:38.489 --> 02:40.120
YEAH, I DO.
THEY'RE MY FRIENDS.

02:40.120 --> 02:41.742
AND THAT RIGHT THERE

02:41.742 --> 02:43.704
IS WHY YOU HAVE NO BUSINESS
IN THAT ROOM.

02:43.704 --> 02:46.086
THERE'S ONLY ONE SET OF FEELINGS
THAT MATTERS HERE,

02:46.086 --> 02:47.708
AND IT'S NOT YOURS.

02:47.708 --> 02:50.751
I DON'T KNOW WHAT'S GONNA
HELP THEM, BUT IT ISN'T YOU.

02:50.751 --> 02:53.133
APRIL KEPNER
IS NO LONGER YOUR PATIENT.

02:53.133 --> 02:55.756
EXCUSE ME.

02:57.468 --> 02:59.300
[ DOOR OPENS ]

03:12.903 --> 03:14.735
April:
[ Crying ] THERE'S NO WAY,

03:14.735 --> 03:18.078
NO WAY FOR ME
TO DO WHAT I NEED TO DO...
APRIL...

03:18.078 --> 03:21.201
...AND WHAT I-I BELIEVE
THAT I SHOULD DO.

03:21.201 --> 03:22.663
Shh, shh, shh.

03:22.663 --> 03:24.585
THERE IS A WAY,
SWEETHEART.

03:24.585 --> 03:26.036
THERE'S ALWAYS A WAY.

03:26.036 --> 03:28.208
NOW,
HERE'S WHAT WE'LL DO.

03:28.208 --> 03:31.211
YOU WILL CHOOSE A DAY.

03:31.211 --> 03:32.543
SOON.

03:32.543 --> 03:36.136
SET IT ASIDE
AND ARRANGE TO BE INDUCED.

03:36.136 --> 03:39.600
AND YOU'LL GIVE BIRTH
TO YOUR BEAUTIFUL LITTLE BOY.

03:39.600 --> 03:41.972
AND YOU'LL GIVE HIM A NAME

03:41.972 --> 03:44.265
AND HAVE HIM BAPTIZED
RIGHT THEN AND THERE.

03:44.265 --> 03:48.188
THEN YOU'RE GONNA GET
TO HOLD THAT BABY.

03:48.188 --> 03:52.112
AND YOU'LL PRAY FOR HIM
AND SING TO HIM.

03:52.112 --> 03:54.315
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK AT HIM.

03:54.315 --> 03:56.737
YOU'RE GONNA LOOK AT HIM

03:56.737 --> 04:00.531
AND MEMORIZE EVERY LITTLE DETAIL
OF HIS FACE.

04:00.531 --> 04:04.825
AND YOU WILL DO THAT
AS LONG AS HE LIVES.

04:04.825 --> 04:10.130
YOU WILL DO THAT
UNTIL GOD TAKES HIM.

04:10.130 --> 04:14.545
THAT'S HOW
YOU WILL DO THIS.

04:14.545 --> 04:16.427
[ SOBS ]
WE CAN DO THAT.

04:16.427 --> 04:18.218
CAN YOU DO THAT FOR ME?

04:18.218 --> 04:20.431
OH, OF COURSE
I'LL DO THAT FOR YOU.

04:20.431 --> 04:23.594
I'LL DO THAT
FOR YOU AND HIM AND US.

04:23.594 --> 04:24.685
OKAY.
OKAY?

04:24.685 --> 04:26.056
OKAY.

04:26.056 --> 04:28.228
SO, I'LL JUST...

04:28.228 --> 04:32.773
I'LL JUST HOLD HIM
UNTIL GOD TAKES HIM.

04:32.773 --> 04:34.355
THAT SOUNDS LOVELY.

04:34.355 --> 04:37.778
MAYBE GOD WON'T TAKE HIM.

04:41.031 --> 04:44.405
MAYBE -- MAYBE
THERE WILL BE A MIRACLE.

04:44.405 --> 04:46.246
OKAY.

04:46.246 --> 04:48.709
I'LL JUST PRAY
FOR A MIRACLE.

04:48.709 --> 04:51.001
OKAY.
OKAY?

04:51.001 --> 04:53.173
[ SOBS ]

04:53.173 --> 04:55.175
OKAY.

04:55.175 --> 04:57.177
OKAY.

05:04.094 --> 05:05.846
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

05:09.099 --> 05:11.021
LORD --

05:11.021 --> 05:12.232
BAILEY!

05:12.232 --> 05:14.234
GREY! WHAT?!

05:14.234 --> 05:16.567
SORRY.
I HAVE A FAVOR TO ASK.

05:16.567 --> 05:18.899
I'M ON CALL THIS WEEKEND.
CAN YOU TAKE IT?

05:18.899 --> 05:21.071
WHY?
WHAT DO YOU NEED TO DO?
I WANT TO GO SEE DEREK.

05:21.071 --> 05:22.533
I DON'T REALLY WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT IN HERE.

05:22.533 --> 05:23.994
NO, I CAN'T.

05:23.994 --> 05:25.245
LITTLE TUCK
IS WITH HIS FATHER,

05:25.245 --> 05:27.077
AND BEN AND I HAVE THE WEEKEND
TO OURSELVES.

05:27.077 --> 05:28.749
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY
I'M ASKING --

05:28.749 --> 05:31.001
THEN YOU KNOW
EXACTLY WHY I'M SAYING NO.

05:31.001 --> 05:32.162
HUH!

05:34.164 --> 05:36.166
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

05:36.166 --> 05:37.418
LORD --

05:37.418 --> 05:39.219
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

05:41.131 --> 05:44.134
OH, WELL, CRAP.

05:44.134 --> 05:46.597
YOU KNOW WHAT I WAS GONNA SAY.

05:49.430 --> 05:51.972
Woman: SOMEBODY GET ME
AN O.R., PLEASE?

05:51.972 --> 05:55.235
MOVE BEDS THREE AND FOUR
TO THE BURN CENTER.

05:55.235 --> 05:57.147
Man: COMING THROUGH!
IT'S A MESS IN HERE.

05:57.147 --> 05:58.479
YEAH, KEPNER'S OUT.

05:58.479 --> 05:59.860
THINGS DON'T RUN RIGHT
WITHOUT HER.

05:59.860 --> 06:01.572
WE HAVE A GSW IN FIVE.
BAILEY, CAN YOU TAKE THAT?

06:01.572 --> 06:03.744
YEAH, B- B-BUT HOW ARE THEY --
KEPNER AND AVERY?

06:03.744 --> 06:06.116
NO WORD.
I'M ADMITTING
THAT FEMUR BREAK IN BED SIX.

06:06.116 --> 06:08.328
BED FIVE NEEDS A RT CONSULT.
OKAY, HOLD ON.
HOLD ON, UM --

06:08.328 --> 06:09.990
OKAY, WELL, WHERE'S KEPNER?
I CAN JUST TELL HER.

06:09.990 --> 06:12.122
UH, SHE AND AVERY
ARE OUT TODAY.

06:12.122 --> 06:13.954
OH, GOD, TODAY?
[ SIGHS ]

06:13.954 --> 06:16.046
OKAY,
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO FOR THEM?

06:16.046 --> 06:17.588
FLOWERS?
NO, THAT'S WEIRD.

06:17.588 --> 06:19.049
YEAH, NO,
W-WHAT ELSE CAN WE DO FOR THEM?

06:19.049 --> 06:21.001
DO FOR WHO?
Together:
KEPNER AND AVERY.

06:21.001 --> 06:23.133
OH, GOD, WHAT DO YOU DO?
FLOWERS?

06:23.133 --> 06:24.214
VETOED.
FOOD?

06:24.214 --> 06:26.346
WHO COOKS?
NOBODY COOKS.

06:26.346 --> 06:27.307
OH, KEPNER COOKS.

06:27.307 --> 06:28.849
WE COULD DO
A FRUIT BASKET?

06:28.849 --> 06:30.220
OH, STOP.
WE COULD ALL SIGN A CARD.

06:31.061 --> 06:34.645
OKAY, I'M STOPPING.
I LIT A CANDLE
IN THE CHAPEL.

06:34.645 --> 06:36.066
IT MADE ME FEEL BETTER.

06:36.066 --> 06:38.398
YOU CAN ALL JUST, UM,
GIVE THEM PRIVACY.

06:38.398 --> 06:41.111
THAT'S ALL
THEY'RE GONNA WANT.

06:43.283 --> 06:44.575
UH, SHEPHERD.

06:44.575 --> 06:46.487
UH, YOU SAID YOU WANTED

06:46.487 --> 06:48.328
TO GO OVER DR. HERMAN'S
TUMOR PLAN.

06:48.328 --> 06:49.580
YOU WANT TO GET LUNCH?
OH.

06:49.580 --> 06:51.992
UH...I CAN'T.

06:51.992 --> 06:54.034
I-I GOT TO PUSH IT.

06:58.999 --> 07:01.542
DREW HAWKINS,

07:01.542 --> 07:04.715
IN FOR A SURGICAL RESECTION
OF A BUTTERFLY GLIOMA.

07:04.715 --> 07:07.137
CAN YOU SEE THE LIGHT
EVEN A LITTLE?

07:07.137 --> 07:10.050
NOPE.
IT'S JUST BLACK.

07:10.050 --> 07:12.853
TOTAL BLINDNESS NOW
FOR ABOUT A MONTH.

07:12.853 --> 07:15.055
BUT I CAN STILL SMELL.

07:15.055 --> 07:17.978
WHAT IS THAT,
LILAC PERFUME?

07:17.978 --> 07:19.690
LAVENDER SHAMPOO.

07:19.690 --> 07:21.862
AND WHY HAS DREW
GONE BLIND?

07:21.862 --> 07:23.193
THE BLINDNESS
IN BOTH EYES

07:23.193 --> 07:25.065
IS CAUSED BY A LESION
IN THE OPTIC RADIATION.

07:25.065 --> 07:26.987
NAILED IT, DR. LAVENDER.
[ CHUCKLES ]

07:26.987 --> 07:28.278
OH, CAN WE SHOW HER
THE TRICK?

07:28.278 --> 07:31.121
SURE.

07:31.121 --> 07:32.703
CATCH!

07:32.703 --> 07:34.915
OH, WOW.
PRETTY FLY
FOR A BLIND GUY, RIGHT?

07:34.915 --> 07:37.037
HOW?
DREW HAS
CORTICAL BLINDNESS.

07:37.037 --> 07:39.129
HIS EYES STILL SEE,
BUT ONLY THE SUBCONSCIOUS PART

07:39.129 --> 07:40.290
OF HIS BRAIN
RECEIVES THE SIGNALS.

07:40.290 --> 07:42.212
YOUR SUBCONSCIOUS
SAW THE PEN.

07:42.212 --> 07:43.544
ONCE I DECOMPRESS THE TUMOR,

07:43.544 --> 07:45.926
I MAY BE ABLE
TO FREE UP THE VISUAL CORTEX,

07:45.926 --> 07:47.347
POSSIBLY RESTORING YOUR SIGHT.

07:47.347 --> 07:48.428
AND MAYBE
I'LL SEE AGAIN?

07:48.428 --> 07:50.260
DREW,
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

07:50.260 --> 07:52.012
I AM GONNA TRY
FOR TOTAL RESECTION,

07:52.012 --> 07:54.184
BUT AT THE VERY LEAST,
I WILL BUY YOU TIME.

07:54.184 --> 07:56.226
I KNOW, I KNOW,
BUT THERE'S A CHANCE?

07:56.226 --> 07:57.808
THERE'S A CHANCE.

08:02.232 --> 08:03.403
[ SIREN WAILING ]
WHAT DO YOU HAVE FOR ME?

08:03.403 --> 08:04.775
BRENDA BONAMAN, 44.

08:04.775 --> 08:06.106
ISOLATED SHOTGUN WOUND
TO THE NECK.

08:06.106 --> 08:07.988
SHE HAS RIGHT SHOULDER
DISLOCATION STATUS

08:07.988 --> 08:09.239
POST MECHANICAL FALL.
WHO SHOT HER?

08:09.239 --> 08:11.111
MY HUSBAND.
YOUR HUSBAND?

08:11.111 --> 08:13.073
NOT LIKE THAT!
NOT ON PURPOSE!

08:13.073 --> 08:14.494
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.
WAS IT, HOWARD?

08:14.494 --> 08:15.536
WAS IT AN ACCIDENT?

08:15.536 --> 08:17.247
DID YOU CONFUSE ME
WITH A MOOSE?

08:17.247 --> 08:19.249
BRENDA, IF I WANTED
TO SHOOT YOU, I'D HAVE
DONE IT IN THE WOODS.

08:19.249 --> 08:21.121
YOU'D STILL BE OUT THERE.
OKAY,
L-LET'S CALM IT DOWN.

08:21.121 --> 08:23.123
Miranda: LET'S GET HER
TO TRAUMA ONE NOW.

08:23.123 --> 08:24.885
SHOULDER DISLOCATION.

08:24.885 --> 08:26.256
THE ACROMION'S FRACTURED.

08:26.256 --> 08:28.088
I'M GONNA NEED TO DO A REDUCTION
UNDER ANESTHESIA.

08:28.088 --> 08:30.220
MIGHT AS WELL WAIT.
SHE'S GOT A ZONE TWO INJURY.

08:30.220 --> 08:32.262
WOUNDS FROM THE CRICOID
TO THE MANDIBLE.

08:32.262 --> 08:33.684
SHE'S GOT TO GO STRAIGHT
TO THE O.R.

08:33.684 --> 08:35.345
OH, GOD.
BRENDA, I'M SORRY.

08:35.345 --> 08:37.097
HOWARD, SHUT UP.
AND, UH...

08:37.097 --> 08:39.139
WHY WERE WE POINTING
A SHOTGUN AT OUR WIFE TODAY?

08:39.139 --> 08:40.691
I WAS PUTTING IT AWAY,
AND IT --

08:40.691 --> 08:42.693
WE HAD JUST COME BACK
FROM DUCK HUNTING.

08:42.693 --> 08:44.695
DUCK HUNTING --
HIS BIG IDEA OF AN ADVENTURE.

08:44.695 --> 08:45.816
IT WAS FUN!
YOU HAD --

08:45.816 --> 08:46.987
I WANTED TO GO TO BELIZE.

08:46.987 --> 08:48.198
WELL,
IT RAINS IN BELIZE, TOO.

08:48.198 --> 08:49.910
I DON'T GET SHOT
IN BELIZE!

08:49.910 --> 08:51.241
[ GROANS ]

08:51.241 --> 08:53.033
BRENDA, WHAT'S HURTING?
EVERYTHING HURTS!

08:53.033 --> 08:54.785
DOCTOR, HERE'S
THE X-RAY.
OKAY.

08:54.785 --> 08:56.036
OKAY, YEAH,
IT'S THIS PELLET.

08:56.036 --> 08:57.618
IT'S CLOSE
TO THE MAJOR BLOOD VESSELS.

08:57.618 --> 08:59.289
Miranda: AND WE'LL KNOW FOR SURE
ONCE WE OPEN HER UP.

08:59.289 --> 09:01.251
COME ON, LET'S GO.
OH, GOD!

09:01.251 --> 09:02.212
HOWARD --
BABY.

09:02.212 --> 09:04.004
BRENDA, HONEY, I'M HERE.
I'M SORRY.

09:04.004 --> 09:05.375
ALL RIGHT, WE GOT TO GO.
SIR, COULD YOU MOVE, PLEASE?

09:05.375 --> 09:07.377
WARREN,
FOLLOW UP ON HER LABS.
AND HAVE THEM RUSHED QUICK.

09:07.377 --> 09:09.009
I NEED THEM UPSTAIRS.

09:09.009 --> 09:11.131
IS SHE --
WHAT IS HAPPENING TO HER?!

09:11.131 --> 09:13.093
LISTEN, YOU CAN WAIT
RIGHT OVER THERE, OKAY?

09:13.093 --> 09:14.134
AND, LISTEN, AS --

09:14.134 --> 09:16.386
AS SOON AS WE KNOW SOMETHING,
WE'LL COME GET YOU.

09:16.386 --> 09:18.178
WE ARE GONNA TAKE
VERY GOOD CARE OF HER.

09:18.178 --> 09:19.980
ALL RIGHT.

09:19.980 --> 09:21.732
UM...WHAT DO I DO
WITH THIS?

09:21.732 --> 09:23.273
UH, THAT'S
A PATIENT'S PERSONALS RELEASE.

09:23.273 --> 09:24.815
BUT, UH, YOU TAKE IT
TO THE CLERK.

09:24.815 --> 09:26.316
BUT FIRST,
TAKE THESE UP TO THE LAB.

09:26.316 --> 09:28.278
TELL THEM TO RUSH THE RESULTS.
YOU GOT IT?

09:35.365 --> 09:38.368
WHAT TIME DID YOU COME
TO BED LAST NIGHT?

09:38.368 --> 09:41.581
I DIDN'T
UNTIL THIS MORNING.

09:41.581 --> 09:44.334
UGH,
MY PALMS ARE SO SWEATY.

09:44.334 --> 09:47.007
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
HI.

09:47.007 --> 09:52.052
SO, I JUST NEED A FEW SIGNATURES
BEFORE WE BEGIN.

09:52.052 --> 09:56.596
UM, SO, WHAT EXACTLY HAPPENS
AFTER THIS?

09:56.596 --> 09:58.178
HOW DO WE GET STARTED?

09:58.178 --> 09:59.980
WELL, UH,
AFTER WE'RE DONE HERE,

09:59.980 --> 10:01.391
I WILL TAKE YOU
TO YOUR ROOM.

10:01.391 --> 10:04.104
I'LL GIVE YOU THE MEDICATION
THAT STARTS DILATION,

10:04.104 --> 10:05.525
THEN THE PITOCIN.

10:05.525 --> 10:08.148
AND YOUR BODY WILL KNOW
WHAT TO DO FROM THERE.

10:08.148 --> 10:12.232
SO, THIS IS
FOR THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE.

10:12.232 --> 10:13.994
HAVE YOU DECIDED
ON A NAME?

10:13.994 --> 10:16.406
UH, WE ARE STILL WORKING
ON THAT.
WE'RE -- YEAH.

10:16.406 --> 10:17.828
OKAY, WELL,
YOU CAN JUST SIGN NOW

10:17.828 --> 10:18.999
AND WE'LL
FILL IN THE REST LATER.

10:18.999 --> 10:22.582
UH, THESE ARE
THE CONSENT FORMS.

10:22.582 --> 10:24.414
I THINK WE SIGNED THOSE.
NOT THESE.

10:24.414 --> 10:27.748
UH, WHAT WE'RE DOING TODAY
IS AN INDUCTION TERMINATION.

10:27.748 --> 10:30.420
YOU'RE AT 24 WEEKS,
SO, TECHNICALLY,

10:30.420 --> 10:33.213
WE COULD INTERVENE
TO KEEP THE BABY ALIVE

10:33.213 --> 10:34.214
AFTER THE DELIVERY.

10:34.214 --> 10:36.346
AND THESE ARE JUST FORMS

10:36.346 --> 10:38.388
TO MAKE IT OFFICIAL
THAT...YOU DON'T.

10:43.263 --> 10:45.435
I NEED BOTH SIGNATURES.

10:45.435 --> 10:47.067
WHAT ARE
THOSE OTHER FORMS?

10:47.067 --> 10:48.819
UH...

10:48.819 --> 10:52.152
THESE ARE, UM...
FOR THE DEATH CERTIFICATE.

10:52.152 --> 10:53.113
REALLY?

10:53.113 --> 10:55.535
CAN WE NOT...YET?

10:55.535 --> 10:57.037
IT'S BETTER

10:57.037 --> 10:59.619
TO GET ALL OF THE PAPERWORK
OUT OF THE WAY,

10:59.619 --> 11:01.621
AND THEN YOU NEVER HAVE TO WORRY
ABOUT IT AGAIN.

11:01.621 --> 11:04.284
DO YOU NEED A MINUTE?

11:04.284 --> 11:05.585
YES, PLEASE.

11:10.630 --> 11:13.053
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

11:13.053 --> 11:15.716
ALL I WANTED WAS
TO START A FAMILY WITH YOU.

11:15.716 --> 11:17.297
OH, I KNOW.

11:17.297 --> 11:18.929
I KNOW.

11:18.929 --> 11:20.180
THIS ISN'T FAIR.

11:20.180 --> 11:22.102
NONE OF THIS IS FAIR.

11:22.102 --> 11:24.805
YOU'RE RIGHT.
I KNOW.

11:33.073 --> 11:34.815
I DON'T CARE WHAT SHE SAYS.

11:34.815 --> 11:36.026
I'M NOT SIGNING THESE.

11:45.165 --> 11:46.827
Jo: I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
THIS PLACE WAS HERE.

11:46.827 --> 11:48.628
Shh.

11:48.628 --> 11:51.001
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

11:51.001 --> 11:52.833
OKAY, LET'S GO.

11:52.833 --> 11:55.095
Shh.

11:59.299 --> 12:01.842
I FOUND IT FIRST --

12:01.842 --> 12:03.433
THEIR BABY'S PROBLEM.

12:03.433 --> 12:05.145
I KNOW,
BUT THAT ISN'T --

12:05.145 --> 12:07.307
I WISHED HORRIBLE THINGS
FOR THEM, JO.

12:07.307 --> 12:09.309
JACKSON LEFT ME FOR HER,

12:09.309 --> 12:13.483
AND I WISHED THEM MISERY
AND FIGHTS AND BREAKUPS.

12:13.483 --> 12:14.524
I MEAN, I'D SEE THEM

12:14.524 --> 12:16.196
SITTING TOGETHER
IN THE CAFETERIA,

12:16.196 --> 12:18.118
AND I'D WISH THEM
FOOD POISONING.

12:18.118 --> 12:20.120
THEN I FOUND THIS.

12:20.120 --> 12:22.202
YOU WOULD
NEVER HAVE WISHED THEM THIS.

12:22.202 --> 12:23.703
[ SIGHS ]
YOU KNOW THAT.

12:23.703 --> 12:26.166
IF YOU HADN'T HAVE FOUND IT,
SOMEBODY ELSE WOULD HAVE.

12:26.166 --> 12:28.078
IT WOULDN'T HAVE CHANGED
ANYTHING.

12:28.078 --> 12:30.210
IT'S NOT ON YOU.

12:30.210 --> 12:33.463
IF ANYTHING, IT JUST MEANS
THAT YOU'RE A GOOD DOCTOR.

12:36.006 --> 12:37.717
OKAY.

12:37.717 --> 12:41.051
I'M GONNA GO
MAKE A BLIND MAN SEE.

12:41.051 --> 12:42.883
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

12:50.811 --> 12:53.153
ZOLA'S GONNA PUSH
FOR COOKIES AFTER DINNER.

12:53.153 --> 12:54.194
DON'T FALL FOR IT.

12:54.194 --> 12:55.856
AND BAILEY'S BLANKET
IS IN THE DRYER.

12:55.856 --> 12:57.027
YEAH, WHY DON'T YOU
TELL THIS TO JO?

12:57.027 --> 12:58.448
SHE'S GONNA BE DOING IT.
WHAT?

12:58.448 --> 13:00.700
YOU OFFERED.
I DIDN'T OFFER.
JO DID.

13:00.700 --> 13:02.242
I'M ON CALL ALL WEEKEND.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:02.242 --> 13:04.164
I CAN'T LEAVE MY KIDS
WITH WILSON.

13:04.164 --> 13:05.205
WILSON IS A HOODLUM.

13:05.205 --> 13:06.827
I LEAVE MY KIDS
WITH MY PERSON.

13:06.827 --> 13:08.578
CRISTINA DID IT
ALL THE TIME.
[ CELLPHONE VIBRATING ]

13:08.578 --> 13:10.000
CRISTINA YANG
WATCHED YOUR KIDS?
YES.

13:10.000 --> 13:11.711
I DON'T BUY THAT
FOR A SECOND.

13:11.711 --> 13:13.914
TALK TO JO.
NO JO!

13:13.914 --> 13:17.417
SHE ASKED YOU
TO WATCH HER KIDS?

13:17.417 --> 13:19.129
YEAH,
SHE'S WIGGING OUT

13:19.129 --> 13:20.921
ABOUT TRYING TO GO TO D.C.
TO SEE DEREK.

13:20.921 --> 13:22.512
WHY DIDN'T SHE ASK ME?
I'M A PERSON.

13:22.512 --> 13:24.424
[ SCOFFS ]
THAT'S NOT WHAT SHE MEANT.
WHAT --

13:24.424 --> 13:26.056
AND YOU DON'T WANT TO BE,
TRUST ME.

13:26.056 --> 13:28.228
IT'S A PAIN IN THE ASS.

13:30.060 --> 13:31.431
[ BRENDA YELLING, GROANING ]

13:31.431 --> 13:32.893
ALL RIGHT,
LET'S GET HER PREPPED.

13:32.893 --> 13:34.734
WE NEED TO PUT HER UNDER.
IT HURTS.
IT HURTS!

13:34.734 --> 13:35.775
OKAY, WE KNOW,

13:35.775 --> 13:36.897
BUT WE'RE GONNA PUT YOU
TO SLEEP,

13:36.897 --> 13:37.988
AND THEN WE CAN ATTEND
TO THAT SHOULDER.

13:37.988 --> 13:39.199
NO, NO, MY STOMACH!

13:39.199 --> 13:40.820
UH, HOLD THE ANESTHESIA.

13:40.820 --> 13:42.572
SHE'S COMPLAINING
OF ABDOMINAL PAIN.

13:42.572 --> 13:43.864
I'M HERE.
WHERE DO YOU NEED ME?

13:43.864 --> 13:45.205
UH, CAN YOU BRING
THE ULTRASOUND?

13:45.205 --> 13:47.537
ALL RIGHT,
I DON'T SEE ANY WOUNDS

13:47.537 --> 13:50.080
IN HER TORSO
OR HER LEGS OR...

13:50.080 --> 13:51.251
UH, BAILEY?

13:51.251 --> 13:52.792
I DON'T THINK YOU'LL NEED
THAT ULTRASOUND.

13:52.792 --> 13:53.833
COME HERE AND TELL ME

13:53.833 --> 13:55.835
IF I AM SEEING
WHAT I THINK I'M SEEING.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.297
OH, MY GOODNESS.
OH, MY GOODNESS.

13:57.297 --> 13:58.588
WHAT?!
WHAT'S GOING ON?

13:58.588 --> 14:01.091
UH, LET'S PAGE O.B.!
OKAY, OKAY.

14:01.091 --> 14:02.883
BRENDA,
HOW FAR ALONG ARE YOU?
WHAT?

14:02.883 --> 14:04.885
I DON'T KNOW --
WHY DIDN'T YOU TELL US
THAT YOU WERE PREGNANT?

14:04.885 --> 14:06.346
BECAUSE I'M NOT!
THAT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

14:06.346 --> 14:08.268
TELL THEM TO GET HERE FAST!
BRING ME THE STIRRUPS.
YES, DOCTOR.

14:08.268 --> 14:09.930
NO, I'M NOT PREGNANT!

14:09.930 --> 14:12.472
I CANT GET PREGNANT!
I CAN'T HAVE A BABY!

14:12.472 --> 14:13.934
YOU ARE HAVING ONE.

14:13.934 --> 14:15.525
I'M LOOKING AT ITS HEAD
RIGHT NOW.

14:15.525 --> 14:16.776
AAH!

14:16.776 --> 14:18.858
ANDERSON?

14:18.858 --> 14:20.610
THAT'S A LAST NAME
AS A FIRST NAME.

14:20.610 --> 14:22.242
I HATE LAST NAMES
AS FIRST NAMES.

14:22.242 --> 14:24.034
I HAVE A LAST NAME
AS A FIRST NAME.

14:24.034 --> 14:25.986
THIS IS GONNA BE
TOO BIG ON ME.

14:25.986 --> 14:28.448
I SHOULD'VE BROUGHT
SOMETHING FROM HOME.
COME ON.

14:28.448 --> 14:31.041
I STILL LIKE --
NO!

14:31.041 --> 14:32.162
I'M SORRY.

14:32.162 --> 14:34.084
I KNOW
HE'S YOUR FAVORITE UNCLE,

14:34.084 --> 14:35.916
BUT YOU CAN'T NAME A CHILD
NORBERT.

14:35.916 --> 14:37.958
NORBERT'S THE KID THAT GETS
HIS LUNCH MONEY STOLEN.

14:37.958 --> 14:39.920
NOW --
HE'S THE KID THAT GETS PUNCHED
ON THE PLAYGROUND.

14:39.920 --> 14:42.212
THAT'S NOT GONNA BE
OUR KID.

14:43.763 --> 14:46.096
[ DOOR OPENS ]
ALL RIGHT, READY FOR...

14:47.557 --> 14:49.059
[ SIGHS ]

14:51.471 --> 14:53.183
I'LL COME BACK.

14:54.644 --> 14:55.775
OKAY.

14:55.775 --> 14:57.107
I THINK IT'S TIME
TO PUT ON THE GOWN.

14:57.107 --> 14:58.228
NO, IT'S NOT TIME.

14:58.228 --> 14:59.729
WE DON'T HAVE A NAME YET.

14:59.729 --> 15:01.111
WE CAN'T DO THIS
WITHOUT A NAME.

15:01.111 --> 15:03.523
WE MAY ONLY HAVE
A COUPLE OF MINUTES

15:03.523 --> 15:05.025
WITH OUR SON ONCE --

15:05.025 --> 15:07.527
I AM NOT GONNA SPEND THAT TIME
TRYING TO FIGURE OUT A NAME.

15:07.527 --> 15:09.619
CAN WE --
JUST GIVE ME --
JUST GIVE ME A MINUTE, OKAY?

15:09.619 --> 15:10.870
JUST WAIT.

15:10.870 --> 15:14.744
I JUST, I WANT...
I JUST WANT TO WAIT IN CASE...

15:14.744 --> 15:17.747
IN CASE WHAT?

15:20.380 --> 15:21.591
IT HAPPENS.

15:21.591 --> 15:24.965
JACKSON, THEY HAPPEN,
ALL RIGHT?

15:24.965 --> 15:29.049
MIR-- MIRACLES, THEY --
THEY HAPPEN TO PEOPLE.

15:29.049 --> 15:31.511
THERE ARE DOCUMENTED
MEDICAL CASES

15:31.511 --> 15:33.763
THAT CANNOT BE EXPLAINED
BY SCIENCE.

15:33.763 --> 15:35.435
WHAT IF THIS IS
ONE OF THOSE AND --

15:35.435 --> 15:37.147
AND WE'RE DECIDING
TO DO THIS TODAY,

15:37.147 --> 15:39.149
WHEN IF WE JUST --

15:39.149 --> 15:41.521
I DON'T EVEN KNOW WHY
I'M TALKING TO YOU ABOUT THIS.

15:41.521 --> 15:42.612
I'M NOT DOING THIS.

15:42.612 --> 15:44.324
I THOUGHT I COULD,
BUT I CAN'T.

15:44.324 --> 15:45.525
I WON'T.
APRIL.

15:45.525 --> 15:46.826
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

15:46.826 --> 15:49.569
Miranda:
OKAY, CALL O.B. AGAIN!

15:49.569 --> 15:50.570
HERE, HOLD PRESSURE.

15:50.570 --> 15:51.992
UH, GET A BABY WARMER
IN HERE.

15:51.992 --> 15:54.204
UH, GOWN US, PLEASE.

15:54.204 --> 15:55.996
HOW DOES SOMEONE
GO THROUGH NINE MONTHS

15:55.996 --> 15:57.287
AND NOT EVEN KNOW
SHE'S PREGNANT?

15:57.287 --> 15:59.289
IT HAPPENS.
HOW DID WE NOT KNOW?

15:59.289 --> 16:01.921
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THOSE DAMN LAB RESULTS?
I DON'T -- I DON'T KNOW!

16:01.921 --> 16:03.083
I GAVE THEM TO AN INTERN,
AND I TOLD HER --

16:03.083 --> 16:05.005
I GAVE THEM TO YOU,
NOT TO AN INTERN.

16:05.005 --> 16:08.048
SO YOU DAMN WELL BETTER FIND OUT
WHAT HAPPENED TO THEM. NOW!

16:10.140 --> 16:12.142
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

16:15.225 --> 16:17.057
WHO THE HELL
LEFT THIS HERE?

16:17.057 --> 16:18.898
UH, WHAT DO YOU NEED?

16:18.898 --> 16:20.360
THIS KIND OF CRAP

16:20.360 --> 16:21.861
WOULD NEVER HAPPEN
WHEN KEPNER'S HERE.

16:21.861 --> 16:23.063
I-I'LL TAKE IT UP THERE.

16:25.025 --> 16:26.656
[ SIGHS ]

16:45.425 --> 16:49.389
SO, IF O.B. DOESN'T GET HERE,
UM, WHO'S CATCHING?

16:49.389 --> 16:51.511
UH, YOU ARE.
OH, I WAS GONNA SAY YOU WERE.

16:51.511 --> 16:53.473
UH, I FIX BONES.
Brenda:
YOU GUYS ARE WRONG!

16:53.473 --> 16:55.095
I'M NOT PREGNANT!

16:55.095 --> 16:56.346
[ SCREAMS ]
IS THAT
ANOTHER CONTRACTION?

16:56.346 --> 16:59.059
NO, MY --
OW, MY SHOULDER!

16:59.059 --> 17:00.520
[ MUTTERS ]

17:00.520 --> 17:02.562
OKAY, MORE LIDOCAINE.

17:02.562 --> 17:05.485
BRENDA, WE CAN'T PUT YOU UNDER
UNTIL THE BABY'S BORN.

17:05.485 --> 17:06.816
ALL RIGHT,
SOMEONE, UH, CALL PEDS!

17:06.816 --> 17:08.648
I'M HAVING A BABY?
I AM?

17:08.648 --> 17:11.611
YES, YOU ARE, BRENDA.
I CAN'T HAVE BABIES.

17:11.611 --> 17:14.074
I WANT TO,
BUT THEY TOLD ME I CAN'T EVER.

17:14.074 --> 17:15.285
OKAY, WELL,
THEY WERE WRONG, SWEETIE.

17:15.285 --> 17:16.866
YOU CAN AND YOU ARE,
SO GET READY.

17:16.866 --> 17:19.289
ON THE NEXT CONTRACTION,
I'M GONNA NEED YOU
TO PUSH, OKAY?

17:19.289 --> 17:21.961
[ GASPS ]
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

17:21.961 --> 17:23.083
PULSE OX IS DROPPING.

17:23.083 --> 17:24.924
THE HEMATOMA'S COMPRESSING
THE TRACHEA.

17:24.924 --> 17:27.297
SHE'S GONNA LOSE HER AIRWAY!
OH, GOD, OKAY.

17:27.297 --> 17:29.008
OKAY, ALL RIGHT,
WE'RE ALMOST THERE, BRENDA.

17:29.008 --> 17:31.010
I WANT YOU
TO PUSH FOR ME, OKAY?

17:31.010 --> 17:32.972
ONE, TWO, THREE, PUSH!

17:32.972 --> 17:35.175
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]
THAT'S GREAT.
THAT'S GREAT.

17:35.175 --> 17:37.937
OKAY, TRY IT AGAIN.
ONE, TWO, THREE, PUSH!

17:37.937 --> 17:39.099
[ BEEPING CONTINUES ]

17:39.099 --> 17:41.811
NO! NO, NO, NO.
DON'T PUSH.

17:41.811 --> 17:43.893
SHE'S STRAINING TOO HARD.
SHE'S DISLODGED THE CLOT.

17:43.893 --> 17:45.945
UH, LAP PADS, LAP PADS.

17:45.945 --> 17:47.357
HOLD PRESSURE WITH ME HERE.

17:47.357 --> 17:49.149
BAILEY.
BAILEY, IT'S OKAY.

17:49.149 --> 17:51.781
IT'S OKAY.
YOU DID IT, BRENDA.

17:51.781 --> 17:53.493
YOU DID IT.

17:53.493 --> 17:55.115
BRENDA,
YOU HAVE A LITTLE GIRL.

17:55.115 --> 17:57.197
[ MONITOR BEEPING RAPIDLY ]

18:06.126 --> 18:08.007
HEY, YOU KNOW
HOW THIS IS DONE?

18:08.007 --> 18:10.009
NOT A CLUE.

18:10.009 --> 18:13.213
HEY, UH, DID YANG
EVER WATCH MEREDITH'S KIDS?

18:13.213 --> 18:14.514
[ SCOFFS, CHUCKLES ]

18:14.514 --> 18:16.136
SEE, I KNEW IT.
MER'S FULL OF CRAP.

18:16.136 --> 18:18.057
I DON'T HAVE TO BABYSIT
FOR HER.
NO, NO, SHE DID.

18:18.057 --> 18:20.890
CRISTINA WOULD TAKE ZOLA.
SHE'D TAKE HER HOME.

18:20.890 --> 18:22.932
AND THEN WHEN
THE DIAPER BLEW OUT,

18:22.932 --> 18:26.025
SHE'D HOLD HER UP TO ME
LIKE A BAG OF MEDICAL WASTE.

18:26.025 --> 18:27.437
CRISTINA WOULD STUDY.

18:27.437 --> 18:29.609
SHE'D EAT
ALL OF ZOLA'S SNACKS.

18:29.609 --> 18:31.321
AND I WOULD BE THE ONE
DOWN ON THE FLOOR

18:31.321 --> 18:33.072
PLAYING WITH BLOCKS,
SO YES AND NO.

18:33.072 --> 18:34.614
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
THIS WEEKEND?

18:34.614 --> 18:37.036
I'D DO IT FOR CRISTINA,
I'M NOT DOING IT FOR YOU.

18:45.004 --> 18:46.746
DAMN IT.

18:52.672 --> 18:53.803
SO, HIS EYES STILL WORK,

18:53.803 --> 18:55.425
IT'S JUST THE COMMUNICATION
TO THE BRAIN?

18:55.425 --> 18:57.056
BUT HIS TUMOR'S
IN THE CORPUS CALLOSUM,

18:57.056 --> 18:58.718
PUSHING
INTO BOTH OCCIPITAL LOBES.

18:58.718 --> 19:00.220
RIGHT.
HE'LL PROBABLY
NEVER SEE AGAIN.

19:00.220 --> 19:02.222
BUT YOU SAID --
I SAID WE'D TRY.

19:02.222 --> 19:04.974
WHAT'S THIS?
TAKING ON NEW CASES?

19:04.974 --> 19:07.607
YOU TOLD ME YOU WERE GOING
"ALL MY TUMOR, ALL THE TIME."

19:07.607 --> 19:09.148
GIVING UP ON ME?
ON THE CONTRARY.

19:09.148 --> 19:11.110
I'M GOING TO USE
A CO2 LASER

19:11.110 --> 19:13.733
TO PEEL A MAN'S GLIOMA OFF
LAYER BY LAYER.

19:13.733 --> 19:16.196
IT'S THE SAME TECHNIQUE I'LL
BE USING ON YOUR OPTIC NERVE.

19:16.196 --> 19:17.577
IT'S HOW I'LL KEEP YOU
FROM GOING BLIND

19:17.577 --> 19:19.239
WHEN I SAVE YOU.
AH.

19:19.239 --> 19:21.741
AND HERE, I THOUGHT I'D WON
YOU OVER TO THE DARK SIDE.

19:21.741 --> 19:24.083
NEVER.
KEEP HOPE ALIVE.

19:24.083 --> 19:27.086
SO, WE'RE PRACTICING
ON HIM?

19:27.086 --> 19:28.878
ON DREW FOR HERMAN?

19:28.878 --> 19:30.049
EVEN THOUGH YOU DON'T THINK
HE'S GONNA SEE AGAIN.

19:30.049 --> 19:31.711
THAT'S ONE WAY
TO LOOK AT IT.

19:31.711 --> 19:33.293
ANOTHER WAY
IS WE'RE GIVING HIM TIME --

19:33.293 --> 19:34.674
MORE YEARS TO LIVE.

19:34.674 --> 19:35.925
LET'S GO.

19:35.925 --> 19:38.678
HAVE RADIOLOGY SEND EVERYTHING
UP TO THE O.R.

19:38.678 --> 19:40.760
[ BABY CRYING ]
OKAY, PUT HER OUT.

19:40.760 --> 19:42.061
LET'S INTUBATE!
WAIT, WAIT,
CAN I HOLD HER?

19:42.061 --> 19:44.394
I'M HERE! GLOVE ME.
OKAY, WE NEED
TO HELP YOU BREATHE NOW.

19:44.394 --> 19:45.805
I JUST NEED TO SEE HER.

19:45.805 --> 19:48.187
I NEED TO HOLD HER.
SHE'S CRYING.

19:48.187 --> 19:49.769
WHERE'S MY BABY?

19:49.769 --> 19:51.150
NO -- OH, NO.

19:51.150 --> 19:52.942
I'M -- I'M GONNA TAKE HER
AND DO AN EXAM.

19:52.942 --> 19:54.694
SHE'LL BE HERE
WHEN YOU WAKE UP, OKAY?

19:54.694 --> 19:55.905
LET ME HOLD MY BABY!

19:55.905 --> 19:57.737
LOOK, IF WE DO,
SHE MIGHT LOSE YOU, HONEY.

19:57.737 --> 19:59.118
THERE'S NO TIME.
LET US WORK.

19:59.118 --> 20:00.159
PLEASE --

20:00.159 --> 20:01.531
I'M SO SORRY, BRENDA.

20:01.531 --> 20:03.373
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

20:03.373 --> 20:05.535
SHE'S THROWING
MULTIFOCAL PVCs.

20:05.535 --> 20:08.167
WHAT THE HELL!
UH, IT'S PROBABL--

20:08.167 --> 20:10.089
UM, ULTRASOUND!

20:10.089 --> 20:12.672
HERE.
LET ME HAVE THOSE FILMS.
OKAY.

20:17.096 --> 20:19.008
WHERE ARE YOU?

20:19.008 --> 20:20.139
OH, DAMN IT.

20:20.139 --> 20:21.391
WHERE IS WHAT?

20:21.391 --> 20:23.393
THERE WAS A PELLET
AT THE VESSELS.

20:23.393 --> 20:26.015
IT SHOULD BE RIGHT THERE,
AND IT ISN'T.

20:26.015 --> 20:27.186
WHICH MEANS IT MOVED
INTO HER HEART.

20:27.186 --> 20:29.148
[ RAPID BEEPING ]

20:29.148 --> 20:31.901
RUNS OF V-TACH!
OKAY, UH, 75 OF LIDO.

20:31.901 --> 20:33.853
LET'S GET
A REPEAT CHEST FILM!

20:33.853 --> 20:35.695
PAGE CARDIO!

20:35.695 --> 20:38.027
BRENDA,
NO MORE SURPRISES!

20:38.027 --> 20:39.949
IT WAS A URINE SAMPLE
AND TWO BLOOD DRAWS.

20:39.949 --> 20:41.821
I-I GAVE IT TO AN INTERN,
AND I TOLD HER TO --

20:41.821 --> 20:43.413
I FOUND IT SITTING
ON A SUPPLY RACK.

20:43.413 --> 20:45.124
WHICH INTERN?
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW.

20:45.124 --> 20:48.708
SHE WAS ABOUT THIS TALL,
DARK HAIRED?

20:48.708 --> 20:50.500
HEY, RICHARD.
WHEN YOU FIND HER, FIND ME.

20:50.500 --> 20:52.632
NO, WHEN I FIND HER,
I'M GONNA KILL HER.

20:52.632 --> 20:53.963
HI.

20:53.963 --> 20:55.084
SO, I'M ON CALL
THIS WEEKEND,

20:55.084 --> 20:56.336
AND I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU COULD TAKE IT.

20:56.336 --> 20:58.718
OH, I'M SORRY.
I MIGHT HAVE PLANS.

20:58.718 --> 21:01.381
CATHERINE AVERY'S IN TOWN,
AND SHE'S GOING THROUGH HELL.

21:01.381 --> 21:02.842
AND I'D LIKE TO BE ABLE
TO TELL HER

21:02.842 --> 21:04.514
I'LL BE AVAILABLE
IF SHE NEEDS ME FOR ANYTHING.

21:04.514 --> 21:06.055
NEVER MIND.
I'LL FIND SOMEONE ELSE.

21:06.055 --> 21:07.887
I-IS THERE A PROBLEM?
I-IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.

21:07.887 --> 21:09.559
WE CAN JUST DROP IT.
EVERYTHING OKAY?

21:09.559 --> 21:10.810
YEAH, IT'S FINE.
REALLY?

21:10.810 --> 21:13.102
YOU CAN TELL ME.
I'D RATHER NOT.

21:13.102 --> 21:14.774
YOU SAID
IT WAS IMPORTANT.

21:14.774 --> 21:16.776
IT'S JUST, MM, SEX.

21:16.776 --> 21:17.657
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

21:17.657 --> 21:20.860
EMERGENCY SEX
WITH MY HUSBAND.

21:20.860 --> 21:22.862
SHOULD'VE DROPPED IT.
TOLD YOU.

21:22.862 --> 21:24.534
[ SIREN WAILING ]

21:25.905 --> 21:27.036
APRIL.

21:27.036 --> 21:28.207
JUST WAIT.
LET ME GO.

21:28.207 --> 21:30.079
OKAY, YOU'RE RIGHT
ABOUT MIRACLES, OKAY?

21:30.079 --> 21:32.081
SOMETIMES THEY HAPPEN.

21:32.081 --> 21:33.873
THERE ARE HEARTS
THAT START BEATING AGAIN.

21:33.873 --> 21:37.006
THERE'S CANCER
THAT JUST GOES AWAY ON ITS OWN.

21:37.006 --> 21:39.178
I KNOW.
I'VE SEEN IT.

21:39.178 --> 21:40.800
IT HAPPENS SOMETIMES.

21:40.800 --> 21:44.884
BUT THIS, APRIL --
THIS IS NOT THAT.

21:44.884 --> 21:47.226
I KNOW.

21:49.138 --> 21:52.642
THIS ISN'T FAIR.

21:52.642 --> 21:56.105
IT ISN'T...JUST.

21:56.105 --> 22:02.031
AND I HAVE SPENT MY LIFE
BELIEVING IN A GOD WHO IS JUST.

22:02.031 --> 22:05.365
HE GAVE ME A CALLING,
AND I FOLLOWED IT.

22:05.365 --> 22:07.246
I SAVE LIVES EVERY DAY.

22:07.246 --> 22:09.949
I FEEL LIKE I'M --
I'M FINALLY BECOMING THE PERSON

22:09.949 --> 22:11.541
THAT HE WANTS ME TO BE.

22:11.541 --> 22:15.334
AND THEN THIS --
TO BE HANDED THIS?

22:17.417 --> 22:20.960
IT'S CRUEL.

22:20.960 --> 22:24.764
[ Crying ] I FEEL LIKE GOD
IS LAUGHING AT ME.

22:24.764 --> 22:27.847
IF THIS IS A TEST,
I FAIL.

22:27.847 --> 22:29.308
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

22:29.308 --> 22:33.102
ALL THOSE YEARS TRUSTING
AND BELIEVING

22:33.102 --> 22:35.605
AND PRAYING...

22:37.817 --> 22:41.481
AND IF THIS --
IF THIS WERE JUST,

22:41.481 --> 22:44.323
EVEN A TINY BIT,
THEN I COULD MAYBE...

22:44.323 --> 22:48.117
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

22:48.117 --> 22:51.120
I CAN'T.
I HAVE TO GO BACK TO WORK.

22:51.120 --> 22:53.332
I HA--
I HAVE TO GO TO WORK.

22:59.048 --> 23:00.630
[ BABIES CRYING ]

23:00.630 --> 23:03.052
YOU'RE MESSING WITH ME.
I'M NOT.

23:03.052 --> 23:05.304
YOU ARE.
I'M NOT.

23:05.304 --> 23:07.176
THAT'S YOUR LITTLE GIRL.

23:07.176 --> 23:08.558
IT'S A MISTAKE.

23:08.558 --> 23:10.640
BRENDA COULDN'T HAVE A BABY.
SHE WASN'T PREGNANT!

23:10.640 --> 23:11.931
SHE WAS AND SHE DID.

23:11.931 --> 23:14.143
IT WAS YOUR WIFE --
SHOTGUN WOUND.

23:14.143 --> 23:16.726
HAD A BABY.
NO, SHE COULDN'T GET
PREGNANT!

23:16.726 --> 23:19.278
WE TRIED!

23:19.278 --> 23:20.570
FOR YEARS!

23:20.570 --> 23:23.152
WE SAW DOCTORS.
ALL OF THEM SAID WE COULDN'T.

23:23.152 --> 23:26.405
AND BRENDA WAS SO...SAD.

23:26.405 --> 23:31.160
AND MAD, AT HERSELF, AND AT ME
'CAUSE WE CAN'T HAVE A BABY.

23:31.160 --> 23:32.992
YOU DO.

23:32.992 --> 23:34.373
WE DIDN'T KNOW IT?

23:34.373 --> 23:37.036
WE -- WE JUST DIDN'T KNOW
SHE WAS PREGNANT?
IT HAPPENS.

23:41.040 --> 23:43.963
THIS WAS THE WHOLE REASON
FOR THE HUNTING TRIPS

23:43.963 --> 23:47.006
AND THE JET SKIS,
TRIPS TO BALI AND STUFF.

23:47.006 --> 23:50.349
I SAID TO HER,
"BABE, IF IT'S JUST GONNA BE US,

23:50.349 --> 23:52.722
LET'S MAKE US AN ADVENTURE."

23:53.853 --> 23:55.555
BUT SHE REALLY WANTED
A BABY.

23:55.555 --> 23:58.357
WE BOTH DID.

24:02.692 --> 24:04.443
YOU CAN HOLD HER
IF YOU WANT.

24:04.443 --> 24:06.275
YEAH?

24:06.275 --> 24:08.277
YEAH.
YES.

24:08.277 --> 24:10.660
HOW'S MY WIFE?

24:10.660 --> 24:12.201
Maggie: SHE'S GONNA DIE
IF I DON'T GET THAT OUT.

24:12.201 --> 24:14.574
THE PELLET IS BOUNCING
ALL AROUND THE RIGHT VENTRICLE.

24:14.574 --> 24:16.205
THAT'S WHAT'S CAUSING
HER ARRHYTHMIAS.

24:16.205 --> 24:17.707
I'M GONNA HAVE TO
OPEN HER UP.

24:17.707 --> 24:19.288
LET'S GET READY
TO PUT HER ON BYPASS!

24:19.288 --> 24:20.790
DAMN IT,
HOW DID WE GET HERE?

24:20.790 --> 24:23.042
LOOK, SHE HAD A BABY
SHE NEVER HAD A CHANCE TO HOLD,

24:23.042 --> 24:24.463
SO IF YOU COULD JUST --
THAT'S NOT HELPING.

24:24.463 --> 24:26.135
I'LL PREP
THE FEMORAL ARTERY.
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

24:26.135 --> 24:27.507
Maggie: SHE'S ARRESTING!
CRASH CART!

24:29.218 --> 24:32.051
CHARGE TO 200.

24:32.051 --> 24:33.052
HUSBAND WANTS TO KNOW
HOW SHE'S DOING.

24:33.052 --> 24:34.724
CLEAR!
AW, CRAP.

24:34.724 --> 24:36.305
[ FLATLINE ]

24:39.769 --> 24:40.980
I HAVE A PULSE.
WE HAVE SINUS!

24:40.980 --> 24:42.982
SPLASH HER WITH BETADINE.
GET ME SOME TOWELS.

24:42.982 --> 24:44.734
FOR WHAT IT'S WORTH,
THIS IS KIND OF A MIRACLE BABY.

24:44.734 --> 24:46.275
I MEAN, THEY NEVER THOUGHT
THEY COULD HAVE ONE.

24:46.275 --> 24:48.027
SO, YOU MIGHT BE SAVING
A WHOLE FAMILY.

24:48.027 --> 24:49.869
NONE OF THIS
IS HELPING ME!

24:49.869 --> 24:51.490
TEN BLADE!

24:51.490 --> 24:54.033
SHE'S GONNA DIE
IF I DON'T GET THAT OUT.

24:54.033 --> 24:56.035
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]

25:06.796 --> 25:08.798
[ SIGHS ]

25:17.767 --> 25:19.098
GOD...

25:19.098 --> 25:21.400
[ SIGHS ]

25:21.400 --> 25:23.402
[ CHUCKLES ]

25:26.235 --> 25:28.568
I DON'T KNOW.

25:28.568 --> 25:32.031
I DON'T KNOW, UH...

25:32.031 --> 25:36.035
IF YOU'RE
OUT THERE OR NOT, UM,

25:36.035 --> 25:38.457
OR IF YOU CAN EVEN HEAR PEOPLE

25:38.457 --> 25:41.500
WHO DON'T KNOW
IF YOU'RE OUT THERE.

25:41.500 --> 25:44.834
OR IF YOU GIVE A CRAP
ABOUT WHAT THEY SAY.

25:44.834 --> 25:48.968
BUT, UM...GOD, YAHWEH,

25:48.968 --> 25:51.510
BUDDHA, E.T.,
WHATEVER...

25:51.510 --> 25:56.435
APRIL...KNOWS.

25:56.435 --> 25:58.768
RIGHT?
SHE BELIEVES.

25:58.768 --> 26:00.680
AND SHE NEEDS YOU.

26:00.680 --> 26:02.021
SO, UH...

26:07.026 --> 26:10.239
UM, SHOW UP FOR HER?

26:10.239 --> 26:12.241
PLEASE?

26:15.785 --> 26:19.248
SHOW UP FOR APRIL.

26:19.248 --> 26:20.660
SHE LOVES YOU.

26:20.660 --> 26:22.081
SHE NEEDS YOU.

26:22.081 --> 26:25.044
PLEASE, UH...

26:25.044 --> 26:29.168
SHOW UP FOR HER.

26:33.512 --> 26:35.304
PLEASE.

27:06.125 --> 27:09.048
[ SIGHS ]
DIDN'T EXPECT TO SEE YOU HERE.

27:09.048 --> 27:13.632
THEY ASKED ME FOR SOME PRIVACY,
SO...I'M STAYING AWAY.

27:20.639 --> 27:23.222
[ SIGHS ]

27:23.222 --> 27:26.065
WHAT CAN I DO?

27:26.065 --> 27:28.027
HOW MANY MONTHS
HAS IT BEEN

27:28.027 --> 27:30.029
SINCE THAT DAY IN BOSTON?

27:30.029 --> 27:33.442
UM...ABOUT SIX.

27:33.442 --> 27:35.574
SIX MONTHS.

27:35.574 --> 27:37.156
SIX.

27:37.156 --> 27:40.119
YET IT TOOK
SOMETHING LIKE THIS

27:40.119 --> 27:42.702
FOR YOU TO PICK UP A PHONE
AND CALL.

27:42.702 --> 27:45.995
I WANTED TO, UH,
SEVERAL TIMES, I --

27:45.995 --> 27:47.997
RICHARD, I-I-I THINK

27:47.997 --> 27:52.171
WE DON'T NEED TO TALK
ABOUT THAT RIGHT NOW.

27:52.171 --> 27:54.964
OKAY.

28:07.727 --> 28:09.899
IF THERE'S ANY WAY
I CAN HELP...

28:11.150 --> 28:14.153
...IF THERE IS ANYTHING
I CAN DO FOR YOU,

28:14.153 --> 28:17.316
OR FOR THEM...
I'M HERE.

28:17.316 --> 28:19.989
I THINK I JUST WANT
TO BE ALONE.

28:22.201 --> 28:24.413
[ SIGHS ]

28:30.790 --> 28:33.042
Amelia:
AND YOU HAVE TO KEEP THE LASER
MOVING ALL THE TIME.

28:33.042 --> 28:34.593
REMOVE THE TUMOR
CELL BY CELL

28:34.593 --> 28:36.505
LIKE ZAPPING DUST
OFF OF A CARPET.

28:36.505 --> 28:38.427
WITHOUT
SINGEING THE CARPET.
EXACTLY.

28:38.427 --> 28:40.970
NOW, WHEN WE USE THIS
ON HERMAN'S TUMOR,

28:40.970 --> 28:43.182
IT'LL BE ON HER OPTIC CHIASM
AND NERVE.

28:43.182 --> 28:44.894
AND RATHER
THAN RESTORING DREW'S SIGHT,

28:44.894 --> 28:46.345
WE'LL HAVE TO KEEP HER
FROM GOING BLIND.

28:46.345 --> 28:48.727
SEE. THERE.
YOU JUST SAID IT.

28:48.727 --> 28:51.310
SAID WHAT?
YOU SAID
"RESTORING DREW'S SIGHT."

28:51.310 --> 28:53.192
YOU NEED TO LET THAT GO.
I KNEW IT.

28:53.192 --> 28:55.154
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE SAID IT
IF YOU COULDN'T DO IT.

28:55.154 --> 28:57.356
YOU WOULDN'T HAVE EVEN TRIED.
THE TUMOR IS EVERYWHERE.
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

28:57.356 --> 28:58.988
I KNEW THAT 20 MINUTES
INTO THIS SURGERY.

28:58.988 --> 29:01.200
OKAY, SO, WHY DON'T YOU STOP?
WHY ARE YOU STILL WORKING?

29:01.200 --> 29:02.571
TO IMPROVE MY TECHNIQUE.

29:02.571 --> 29:04.203
THAT'S...

29:05.825 --> 29:07.917
YOU SHOULD STOP.
WHY?

29:07.917 --> 29:10.079
YOU DON'T FEEL
THE SLIGHTEST BIT GUILTY?
GUILTY? WHY?

29:10.079 --> 29:11.961
FOR USING
THIS NICE, FUNNY MAN,

29:11.961 --> 29:14.003
FOR TURNING HIM
INTO A SKILLS LAB.

29:14.003 --> 29:16.085
I CAN'T USE A HUMAN BEING
FOR PRACTICE.

29:16.085 --> 29:17.797
YOU FEEL GUILTY

29:17.797 --> 29:19.718
BECAUSE YOU ARE
THINKING ABOUT YOU.

29:19.718 --> 29:21.680
AND THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH YOU.

29:21.680 --> 29:22.681
THIS IS ABOUT DREW.

29:22.681 --> 29:24.143
THIS WAS HIS LAST HOPE.

29:24.143 --> 29:26.435
THE CHANCES WERE SLIM,
AND DREW KNEW THAT.

29:26.435 --> 29:28.597
SO I AM THINKING ABOUT
WHAT TO SAY TO HIM

29:28.597 --> 29:31.020
WHEN HE FINDS OUT THAT
THAT LAST HOPE IS GONE.

29:31.020 --> 29:32.601
THAT IS WHAT
YOU SHOULD BE THINKING ABOUT,

29:32.601 --> 29:33.692
NOT YOUR OWN GUILT.

29:37.857 --> 29:39.198
Maggie: CLAMPS OFF.

29:39.198 --> 29:39.989
UP WITH THE FLOW.

29:39.989 --> 29:41.530
COME ON, START BEATING.
[ FLATLINE ]

29:43.492 --> 29:45.204
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE GONNA HAVE
TO USE SOME ELECTRICITY.

29:45.204 --> 29:47.997
CHARGE THE PADDLES TO 20.

29:47.997 --> 29:50.409
[ ELECTRICITY HUMMING ]

29:50.409 --> 29:51.540
CHARGED.
CLEAR.

29:53.582 --> 29:55.214
OH, GOD.
AGAIN.

29:55.214 --> 29:56.715
HER HEART'S BEEN
THROUGH A LOT TODAY.

29:56.715 --> 29:58.217
SHE GOT SHOT
AND SHE HAD A BABY.

29:58.217 --> 30:00.219
CLEAR!

30:00.219 --> 30:01.800
[ FLATLINE CONTINUES ]

30:09.308 --> 30:11.100
BRENDA!

30:11.100 --> 30:12.852
YOU ARE GOING TO HOLD
YOUR BABY.

30:12.852 --> 30:14.433
DO YOU UNDERSTAND ME?

30:14.433 --> 30:17.857
YOU HAVE A LITTLE GIRL
WHO WANTS TO MEET YOU,

30:17.857 --> 30:20.029
SO YOU ARE GOING TO SHOW UP
FOR THAT

30:20.029 --> 30:22.201
AND YOU ARE GOING
TO HOLD HER.
[ ELECTRICITY HUMMING ]

30:22.201 --> 30:23.322
CLEAR!

30:24.283 --> 30:27.536
I GOT THINGS COVERED.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE HERE IF...

30:27.536 --> 30:29.248
YOU DON'T WANT ME HERE?
NO.

30:29.248 --> 30:31.000
NO, THIS PLACE
DOESN'T WORK WITHOUT YOU.

30:31.000 --> 30:32.541
IT'S BEEN A MESS HERE
TODAY.

30:32.541 --> 30:34.083
I NEED YOU HERE,

30:34.083 --> 30:36.045
BUT NOT IF YOU DON'T NEED
TO BE HERE.

30:36.045 --> 30:37.216
I WANT TO BE HERE.

30:37.216 --> 30:39.048
NO ONE HAS SEEN
MY MYSTERIOUS INTERN.

30:39.048 --> 30:40.459
NO ONE'S EVEN HEARD
OF HER.

30:40.459 --> 30:42.011
I RUN THE E.R.
I KNOW EVERY INTERN.

30:42.011 --> 30:43.012
WHAT'S HER NAME?
I-I DON'T KNOW.

30:43.012 --> 30:44.513
I MEAN, SHE --
SHE'S DARK HAIRED,

30:44.513 --> 30:46.095
SHE'S GOT A VACANT LOOK
ON HER FACE,

30:46.095 --> 30:48.017
AND SHE --
SHE'S RIGHT THERE.

30:48.017 --> 30:49.638
HEY!
HEY, YOU.

30:49.638 --> 30:52.101
WHY DIDN'T YOU DO
WHAT I ASKED YOU TO?
WARREN.

30:52.101 --> 30:53.812
I'M SORRY.
I DON'T KNOW IF...

30:53.812 --> 30:55.314
AND -- AND WHY DO YOU
STILL HAVE THIS?

30:55.314 --> 30:57.606
I TOLD YOU THIS MORNING
TO JUST --
STOP IT RIGHT NOW.

30:59.608 --> 31:01.610
YOU DON'T WORK HERE,
DO YOU?

31:03.112 --> 31:04.033
WHAT'S YOUR NAME?

31:04.033 --> 31:06.155
WENDY.

31:06.155 --> 31:08.577
THESE ARE
PERSONAL RELEASE PAPERS

31:08.577 --> 31:10.289
FOR A DECEASED PATIENT.

31:11.450 --> 31:13.332
WHO IS THIS PATIENT?

31:13.332 --> 31:16.045
MY FIANCé.

31:19.258 --> 31:20.799
YOU CAME IN LAST NIGHT.

31:22.801 --> 31:25.054
I COULDN'T GO HOME.

31:27.136 --> 31:30.099
[ FLATLINE ]

31:30.099 --> 31:32.811
[ SOBBING ]

31:32.811 --> 31:34.853
MICHAEL AND I WERE DRIVING HOME
FROM THIS LODGE.

31:34.853 --> 31:36.685
WE THOUGHT WE MIGHT HAVE
OUR WEDDING THERE.

31:36.685 --> 31:40.569
AND THEN THERE WAS
A BIG TRUCK, AND THEN...

31:40.569 --> 31:43.732
EVERYONE'S
BEEN REALLY NICE.

31:43.732 --> 31:44.903
THEY GOT ME CLEANED UP.

31:44.903 --> 31:46.695
SOMEONE GAVE ME
THESE CLOTHES TO WEAR

31:46.695 --> 31:49.288
BECAUSE MINE
WERE COVERED IN...

31:49.288 --> 31:51.200
I WENT DOWN
TO THE CAFETERIA.

31:51.200 --> 31:53.582
I THINK THEY THOUGHT
I WAS A DOCTOR.

31:53.582 --> 31:55.084
THEY GAVE ME FOOD.

31:55.084 --> 31:59.458
I WENT UPSTAIRS TO THE NURSERY.
I LOOKED AT THE BABIES.

31:59.458 --> 32:02.631
AND IT MADE ME FEEL
A LITTLE BETTER.

32:02.631 --> 32:06.135
I'M SORRY IF I MESSED UP THINGS
FOR THAT ONE DOCTOR.

32:06.135 --> 32:08.887
I WASN'T SURE...

32:12.431 --> 32:14.893
[ Voice breaking ]
THEY TOLD ME I COULD TAKE

32:14.893 --> 32:17.186
MICHAEL'S THINGS HOME WITH ME
WHEN I WAS READY.

32:17.186 --> 32:19.768
I HAVEN'T BEEN READY.

32:19.768 --> 32:22.191
I KNOW.

32:22.191 --> 32:25.154
WE WERE GONNA DO
SO MANY THINGS.

32:25.154 --> 32:26.986
THIS WAS OUR BEGINNING.

32:26.986 --> 32:29.738
WE HAD SO MANY PLANS
FOR A LIFE

32:29.738 --> 32:32.741
AND A FAMILY,
AND NOW THEY'RE GONE!

32:32.741 --> 32:34.203
THEY'RE GONE.

32:34.203 --> 32:36.205
[ SOBS ]

32:38.577 --> 32:41.460
WENDY,
DO YOU BELIEVE IN GOD?

32:41.460 --> 32:43.882
YES.

32:43.882 --> 32:45.884
BUT HE DIDN'T.

32:45.884 --> 32:48.007
MICHAEL DIDN'T BELIEVE.
IT'S OKAY.

32:48.007 --> 32:50.049
YOU CAN BELIEVE ENOUGH
FOR THE TWO OF YOU.

32:50.049 --> 32:53.472
YOU HAVE LOST SOMEBODY,

32:53.472 --> 32:57.146
AND YOU ARE HURTING,

32:57.146 --> 33:00.149
BUT YOU WILL GET
THROUGH THIS.

33:00.149 --> 33:01.480
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

33:01.480 --> 33:04.483
YOU CAN SURVIVE THIS.

33:06.655 --> 33:10.159
YOU ARE STRONG.

33:12.071 --> 33:13.952
IT'S OKAY.

33:13.952 --> 33:18.077
YOU ARE GONNA BE OKAY.

33:18.077 --> 33:20.039
I PROMISE.

33:24.083 --> 33:26.885
April:
SAMUEL NORBERT AVERY.

33:26.885 --> 33:28.887
THAT SHOULD BE
OUR SON'S NAME.

33:28.887 --> 33:30.049
IT SHOULD?
YEAH.

33:30.049 --> 33:34.012
I THINK I GOT
WHAT I WAS WAITING FOR.

33:34.012 --> 33:36.435
YOU DID?

33:36.435 --> 33:39.188
LET'S GO BACK UPSTAIRS.

33:39.188 --> 33:41.230
I'M READY NOW.

33:53.992 --> 33:55.994
[ SIGHS ]

34:06.425 --> 34:07.966
MEREDITH?

34:07.966 --> 34:09.968
UH, MY PLANS HAVE CHANGED.

34:09.968 --> 34:12.010
UH, I'D BE HAPPY
TO TAKE YOUR WEEKEND CALL.

34:12.010 --> 34:14.173
YOU SHOULD GO.
THANKS, BUT IT'S FINE.

34:14.173 --> 34:15.844
I CAN GO ANOTHER TIME.
IT'S NOT A BIG DEAL.
NO, NO.

34:15.844 --> 34:18.056
TAKE IT FROM A MAN
WHO HAS SPENT HIS LIFE

34:18.056 --> 34:20.018
REGRETTING THE FLIGHTS
HE NEVER TOOK.

34:20.018 --> 34:22.811
GET ON THE PLANE,
SEE DEREK.

34:22.811 --> 34:25.354
IT IS A BIG DEAL.

34:25.354 --> 34:28.107
BUT I DON'T HAVE ANYONE
TO WATCH MY KIDS

34:28.107 --> 34:29.568
AND AMELIA IS WORKING, SO --

34:29.568 --> 34:31.029
I AM HERE.
WHAT?

34:31.029 --> 34:32.070
I SAID I'M HERE.

34:32.070 --> 34:34.533
I MOVED HERE ALONE
AND I HAVE MADE ONE FRIEND,

34:34.533 --> 34:36.074
AND I CONSIDER YOU
MY FRIEND.

34:36.074 --> 34:39.288
OH, I-I JUST -- I MEAN,
I DIDN'T EVEN --
NO, I'M JUST SAYING.

34:39.288 --> 34:41.620
IF YOU
EVER NEED SOMETHING,

34:41.620 --> 34:44.203
LIKE IF YOU
EVER NEED HELP MOVING

34:44.203 --> 34:46.125
OR, LIKE, A RIDE TO THE AIRPORT,
LIKE, I'M THAT KIND OF FRIEND.

34:46.125 --> 34:47.626
BUT I CAN'T ASK YOU
TO BABYSIT MY KIDS.

34:47.626 --> 34:49.047
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
I WOULD LOVE TO.

34:49.047 --> 34:50.759
I WAS A GIRL SCOUT,
AND I WAS REGISTERED

34:50.759 --> 34:52.591
WITH A BABYSITTING SERVICE
AS A TEENAGER.

34:52.591 --> 34:54.173
AND I'M GOOD.

34:54.173 --> 34:56.635
I MEAN, I'M A "PLAY ON THE FLOOR
AND COOK FOR THEM" BABYSITTER.

34:56.635 --> 34:57.846
YOU COOK?
AND I BAKE.

34:57.846 --> 34:59.057
KIDS LOVE BAKING,

34:59.057 --> 35:01.140
AND I LOVE BABIES,
AND BABIES LOVE ME.

35:01.140 --> 35:03.021
AND, YOU KNOW,
THEY'RE MY NIECE AND NEPHEW,

35:03.021 --> 35:05.484
SO I WOULD -- I WOULD LOVE TO.
I WOULD LOVE TO.

35:05.484 --> 35:07.606
YOU --
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BAKE.

35:07.606 --> 35:09.188
OKAY, BUT CAN I?

35:10.899 --> 35:12.321
WE WERE PRETTY SUCCESSFUL.

35:12.321 --> 35:15.494
WE WERE ABLE TO REMOVE
ABOUT 98% OF YOUR TUMOR,

35:15.494 --> 35:18.197
SO YOU'VE GOT A FEW MORE YEARS
COMING TO YOU.
OH.

35:18.197 --> 35:19.368
WELL,
I HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE

35:19.368 --> 35:21.039
TO BRING MYSELF
TO OPEN UP MY EYES YET.

35:21.039 --> 35:23.242
WHY DON'T YOU DO THAT NOW?

35:23.242 --> 35:26.004
OKAY.

35:32.511 --> 35:34.513
[ GASPS ]

35:40.429 --> 35:42.601
SOMEBODY SAY SOMETHING
SO I KNOW WHO'S WHO.

35:42.601 --> 35:44.022
YOU CAN SEE?
YEAH.

35:44.022 --> 35:46.144
I-IT'S BLURRY,
BUT IT'S -- YEAH!

35:46.144 --> 35:49.107
OKAY, THAT MAY IMPROVE,
IT MAY NOT.

35:49.107 --> 35:50.979
DREW, WE'LL RUN SOME TESTS,
BUT --

35:50.979 --> 35:54.112
IT'S -- BUT THAT'S -- I DIDN'T
THINK THAT I SHOULD HOPE.

35:54.112 --> 35:56.695
DR. LAVENDER.

35:56.695 --> 35:58.327
[ LAUGHS ]

35:59.828 --> 36:01.200
YOU DID IT.

36:01.200 --> 36:02.581
I -- I MEAN,
I KNEW YOU COULD DO IT.

36:02.581 --> 36:04.953
EVEN WHEN YOU SAID
IT WAS IMPOSSIBLE --
BECAUSE IT WAS.

36:04.953 --> 36:06.205
BUT YOU PULLED IT OFF!

36:06.205 --> 36:07.666
AND YOU SAID TO STOP.

36:07.666 --> 36:08.787
THAT'S THE DIFFERENCE.

36:08.787 --> 36:10.999
I KNOW WHAT IT IS TO WALK
INTO A HOSPITAL O.R.

36:10.999 --> 36:13.171
WITH LITTLE
OR NO CHANCE OF SUCCESS,

36:13.171 --> 36:15.424
TO DO ALL OF THE PLANNING
AND HOPING AND LABOR,

36:15.424 --> 36:17.796
KNOWING THAT IN THE END,
IT MAY AMOUNT TO NOTHING.

36:17.796 --> 36:19.177
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE.

36:19.177 --> 36:20.639
BUT IT IS WHAT
IS ASKED OF US.

36:20.639 --> 36:21.800
AND IF YOU CAN'T DO IT,

36:21.800 --> 36:24.182
IF YOU AREN'T WILLING
TO KEEP LOOKING FOR LIGHT

36:24.182 --> 36:25.974
IN THE DARKEST OF PLACES
WITHOUT STOPPING

36:25.974 --> 36:28.727
EVEN WHEN IT SEEMS IMPOSSIBLE,
YOU WILL NEVER SUCCEED.

36:28.727 --> 36:30.729
WHAT I AM DOING NEXT
WITH HERMAN

36:30.729 --> 36:33.312
IS MUCH, MUCH HARDER
THAN THIS.

36:33.312 --> 36:34.573
I ONLY NEED TO BE BETTER,

36:34.573 --> 36:36.485
AND I AM GONNA GET THERE
ANY WAY I CAN.

36:36.485 --> 36:37.986
IF YOU ARE NOT WILLING
TO DO THAT,

36:37.986 --> 36:39.868
THEN YOU SHOULDN'T BE
WORKING WITH ME

36:39.868 --> 36:41.320
AND YOU PROBABLY
SHOULDN'T BE A SURGEON.

36:41.320 --> 36:43.702
UNDERSTAND?

36:48.287 --> 36:51.290
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

36:51.290 --> 36:52.671
YEP.

36:58.927 --> 37:02.100
HEY, THE CANDLE THING
DOES WORK, BY THE WAY.

37:02.100 --> 37:05.143
SO, THANKS FOR THAT.

37:10.148 --> 37:12.521
[ CRYING SOFTLY ]
HOWARD?

37:12.521 --> 37:14.062
ARE YOU OKAY?

37:14.062 --> 37:15.564
YEAH.

37:15.564 --> 37:16.945
NO.

37:16.945 --> 37:18.617
THIS IS JUST A LOT
FOR ONE DAY.

37:18.617 --> 37:20.949
FOR A LIFETIME.

37:20.949 --> 37:22.120
YOU READY?

37:22.120 --> 37:23.862
YEAH.

37:25.864 --> 37:29.077
[ GASPS ]
OH, THAT'S HER.

37:29.077 --> 37:31.670
SHE'S REAL?

37:31.670 --> 37:33.872
HERE SHE IS.
OH!

37:33.872 --> 37:36.214
HERE'S MAMA.

37:36.214 --> 37:38.006
OH, OH!

37:38.006 --> 37:41.510
LOOK AT YOU.

37:41.510 --> 37:43.432
OH, LOOK AT YOU.

37:43.432 --> 37:45.884
YOU LOOK JUST LIKE
YOUR DADDY.

37:45.884 --> 37:48.056
YOU HAVE HIS NICE CHIN.

37:48.056 --> 37:49.227
[ CHUCKLES ]

37:53.652 --> 37:55.984
OH.

37:55.984 --> 37:58.357
[ MURMURING ]

37:58.357 --> 38:00.449
[ SIGHS ]

38:59.958 --> 39:02.010
HE SQUEEZED MY FINGER.

39:02.010 --> 39:04.092
OH.

39:07.095 --> 39:10.639
AND THEN HE LET GO.

39:10.639 --> 39:14.733
WE CAN'T GET TOO CLOSE.

39:14.733 --> 39:19.187
IF WE FELT EVEN A LITTLE
OF THE LOVE AND THE JOY

39:19.187 --> 39:23.071
AND THE HOPES THAT OUR PATIENTS
ARE SAYING GOODBYE TO...

39:26.324 --> 39:29.698
...WE'D NEVER BE ABLE
TO FUNCTION.

39:29.698 --> 39:31.410
IS IT OVER?
YEAH.

39:31.410 --> 39:33.412
I'M GIVING THEM SOME TIME.

39:33.412 --> 39:35.163
THANK YOU FOR TODAY.

39:35.163 --> 39:37.125
IT THINK THAT IT
WOULD HAVE BEEN HARDER

39:37.125 --> 39:38.046
TO BE IN THERE.

39:38.046 --> 39:39.548
[ SIGHS ]

39:39.548 --> 39:42.761
IT'S...
NEVER EASY FOR ANYBODY.

39:42.761 --> 39:46.765
SO WE SAY,
"WE'RE SORRY FOR YOUR LOSS."

39:52.100 --> 39:55.273
AND WE HOPE
IT OFFERS SOMETHING.

40:10.949 --> 40:14.332
CAN YOU
JUST TAKE ME HOME?

40:14.332 --> 40:18.296
TAKE ME HOME,
TAKE ME TO BED,

40:18.296 --> 40:21.540
AND JUST HOLD ME?

40:21.540 --> 40:24.172
[ SIGHS ]

40:24.172 --> 40:26.545
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

40:32.010 --> 40:34.813
SOME LITTLE BIT OF SUPPORT.

40:34.813 --> 40:36.815
[ SIREN WAILING ]

40:52.160 --> 40:56.334
SOME BIT OF PEACE.

40:59.127 --> 41:02.501
SOME BIT OF CLOSURE.

41:19.057 --> 41:21.900
SOMETHING GOOD.

41:21.900 --> 41:24.482
SOME LITTLE PIECE OF BEAUTY

41:24.482 --> 41:26.985
IN THE MIDST
OF SOMEPLACE DARK.

41:37.455 --> 41:40.118
[ SIGHS ]

41:40.118 --> 41:43.832
MY BABY LIVED
FOR 43 MINUTES.

41:54.683 --> 41:59.057
AN UNEXPECTED GIFT...

41:59.057 --> 42:03.401
JUST WHEN IT'S NEEDED MOST.
